Diet and Nutrition
Our dietician will talk to you about the nutritional requirements during pregnancy, DO’s and DONT’s in the kind of food you consume and advise you on the right kind of diet for your pregnancy. Individualized counseling may be particularly helpful for mothers who are under weight or overweight, diabetic or hypertensive.

The objective is to guide these women through their pregnancy with emphasis on preventive care. Good prenatal preparation and care results in an increased probability of normal deliveries and less problems for the mother and the newborn. Emphasis is placed on offering prenatal education and making the experience of childbirth less stressful and more enjoyable for the entire family. Individual care and attention is offered to healthy women to monitor and guide them. The program also helps mothers to get back into shape after delivery and cope up with motherhood better.